        <div class="content-block">
            <h2>What is Answer Engine Optimisation?</h2>
            <p>Answer Engine Optimisation (AEO) focuses on structuring content to appear in direct answer formats in search results. This includes featured snippets, knowledge panels, and AI-generated answer boxes.</p>
            <p>Search engines increasingly provide direct answers to user queries rather than simply listing links. AEO adapts content to be selected for these prominent positions.</p>
            <p>The goal is to have your content be the source that search engines extract and display when users ask questions related to your expertise or services.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- How AEO Works Section -->
<section class="content-section alt-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-block">
            <h2>How AEO Works</h2>
            <p>Search engines select content for direct answers based on several factors:</p>
            <ul class="content-list">
                <li><strong>Question-Answer Formatting:</strong> Content that directly addresses common questions in clear, concise language</li>
                <li><strong>Structured Data:</strong> Schema markup that helps search engines understand content relationships</li>
                <li><strong>Authority:</strong> Content from sources deemed trustworthy and authoritative on the topic</li>
                <li><strong>Extractability:</strong> Content formatted in ways that can be easily extracted and displayed</li>
                <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> Factually correct information that aligns with consensus sources</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- AEO vs Traditional SEO Section -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-block">
            <h2>AEO vs Traditional SEO</h2>
            <p>AEO builds on traditional SEO but adds specific considerations:</p>
            <ul class="content-list">
                <li><strong>Content Structure:</strong> Traditional SEO focuses on keywords; AEO focuses on question-answer patterns</li>
                <li><strong>Format:</strong> AEO requires content in formats search engines can extract (lists, tables, definitions)</li>
                <li><strong>Precision:</strong> AEO rewards concise, specific answers over comprehensive but lengthy content</li>
                <li><strong>Schema:</strong> AEO relies more heavily on structured data markup</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Effective AEO complements rather than replaces traditional <a href="/">SEO Sydney</a> work. The foundational elements of technical SEO and content quality remain important.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Featured Snippet Types Section -->
<section class="content-section alt-bg">
